Class GameState

java.lang.Object
com.pjv.Model.GameState
public class GameState extends Object
The GameState class represents the state of the game at a certain point in time.

  • Constructor Details

    • GameState

      public GameState(Piece[][] board, int steps, Player currPlayer, int playerTurns, boolean pushCanBeDone, boolean pullCanBeDone, int pushRow, int pushCol, int pushStrength, int pullRow, int pullCol, int pullStrength)
      Constructs a GameState object with the specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      board - the game board
      steps - the number of steps taken
      currPlayer - the current player
      playerTurns - the number of turns played by the current player
      pushCanBeDone - flag indicating if a push move can be performed
      pullCanBeDone - flag indicating if a pull move can be performed
      pushRow - the row index of the piece to be pushed
      pushCol - the column index of the piece to be pushed
      pushStrength - the strength of the push move
      pullRow - the row index of the piece to be pulled
      pullCol - the column index of the piece to be pulled
      pullStrength - the strength of the pull move
